1
00:00:00,950 --> 00:00:03,350
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:06,400
Aye! I'm reporting live from E-Land!

3
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:07,780
Can everyone see this?

4
00:00:07,780 --> 00:00:10,440
I can't believe there's an amusement 
park in the middle of Edolas's castle!

5
00:00:10,440 --> 00:00:12,280
How whacked-out is this King anyway?

6
00:00:13,040 --> 00:00:16,640
It's not all fun, either. You'll 
encounter many things...

7
00:00:16,640 --> 00:00:19,500
Everyone check out all the 
different kinds of attractions!

8
00:01:51,220 --> 00:01:52,750
Edolas.

9
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:57,120
It is a world which is losing its magic.

10
00:01:57,120 --> 00:02:02,890
The people live their lives with 
magic as a limited commodity.

11
00:02:03,170 --> 00:02:07,020
All Wizard Guilds have been disbanded,

12
00:02:07,020 --> 00:02:09,850
but there are still those 
who resist and continue on.

13
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:14,820
And their name is the Dark Guild, Fairy Tail!

14
00:02:17,850 --> 00:02:20,880
And now the curtain has risen

15
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:24,180
on the battle between the Fairy Tail 
wizards that came from Earthland,

16
00:02:24,180 --> 00:02:28,160
and the Magic Regiments of the Royal Army!

17
00:02:40,380 --> 00:02:43,260
Do you return to your cells, or die here?

18
00:02:43,260 --> 00:02:47,150
Sugar Boy, we don't have 
to give them the choice.

19
00:02:47,150 --> 00:02:48,720
Oh, yeah?

20
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:53,630
We've finished extracting 
the dragon's magic power.

21
00:02:54,820 --> 00:03:00,320
If Code ETD is a success, we'll have 
no need for the Dragon Slayers.

22
00:03:01,430 --> 00:03:07,160
You Earthlanders with no concept of 
the value of magic will die here!

23
00:03:10,480 --> 00:03:11,390
The ship?!

24
00:03:32,820 --> 00:03:34,990
It's Life!!!!

25
00:03:44,810 --> 00:03:45,820
An ice shield?

26
00:03:48,850 --> 00:03:51,940
So, this is Earthland magic?

27
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:55,510
You really don't use tools, do you?

28
00:03:56,720 --> 00:03:58,210
I've never seen it before.

29
00:03:59,420 --> 00:04:01,080
There's flames around his legs!

30
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:01,920
Here I come!

31
00:04:08,090 --> 00:04:10,390
Return our friends!

32
00:04:11,220 --> 00:04:12,910
Friends?

33
00:04:12,910 --> 00:04:16,530
Your "friends" will mix with Extalia's magic,

34
00:04:16,530 --> 00:04:19,150
and become an eternal supply of magic power!

35
00:04:19,820 --> 00:04:24,460
Why're you still blabbing about 
that? I said we ain't gonna let you!

36
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:28,020
Natsu, behind you!

37
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,970
What's this?

38
00:04:30,970 --> 00:04:32,450
We're sinking into the floor?

39
00:04:39,460 --> 00:04:41,000
No way that'll hit me!

40
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,660
Oh, we'll see about that.

41
00:04:42,660 --> 00:04:44,760
Hell's Tornado!

42
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:45,760
What?

43
00:04:48,910 --> 00:04:50,270
What the heck?!

44
00:04:50,270 --> 00:04:52,790
It's shooting out the rail it's going along!

45
00:04:52,790 --> 00:04:54,620
He sounds like he's enjoying it...

46
00:04:54,620 --> 00:05:01,660
Anyway, my weapon, the Command Tact, can cause 
all the attractions here to freely move at will!

47
00:05:02,190 --> 00:05:05,110
Who cares if you can move 'em all you want?

48
00:05:05,110 --> 00:05:07,720
All I gotta do is bust 'em up!

49
00:05:07,950 --> 00:05:10,470
That's not good, you imbecile.

50
00:05:10,470 --> 00:05:11,740
What'd you call me?!

51
00:05:11,740 --> 00:05:14,700
There's more than one Hell's Coaster!

52
00:05:14,700 --> 00:05:19,580
And it plays a beautiful 
symphony, which I conduct!

53
00:05:22,910 --> 00:05:24,640
Hey, let me go!

54
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:29,850
This attraction considers the safety 
of its guests its number one priority.

55
00:05:29,850 --> 00:05:31,100
Tee-hee!

56
00:05:33,430 --> 00:05:38,350
Using enough magic power, the Hell's Coaster 
can accelerate to 10 times normal speed.

57
00:05:38,350 --> 00:05:41,650
I don't care who you are, 5 
minutes riding that and...

58
00:05:44,230 --> 00:05:46,440
It hasn't been more than 10 seconds!

59
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:49,480
Whoa, what's with this guy? He's so weak!

60
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:51,320
What is this?

61
00:05:51,570 --> 00:05:53,260
Things aren't going well over there.

62
00:05:53,260 --> 00:05:55,590
We're not doing so well here, either!

63
00:05:55,590 --> 00:05:58,020
Lucy, pull Natsu out of there!

64
00:05:58,020 --> 00:05:59,500
How?

65
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:11,340
You're not going to...

66
00:06:15,060 --> 00:06:17,680
Get going!

67
00:06:28,350 --> 00:06:29,860
Please stop this thing!

68
00:06:32,990 --> 00:06:35,410
This girl is pretty brave...

69
00:06:36,580 --> 00:06:37,910
Natsu!

70
00:06:38,180 --> 00:06:40,080
Lucy, I'm counting on you!

71
00:06:40,450 --> 00:06:43,460
Ice Make Flying Claw!

72
00:06:48,060 --> 00:06:52,720
If you had that kind of magic, wouldn't 
it have been better if you rescued him?

73
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:56,350
Then no one would be around to kick your ass!

74
00:06:57,690 --> 00:06:59,680
You have quite the confidence.

75
00:07:00,690 --> 00:07:04,590
Ice Make Death Scythe!

76
00:07:13,470 --> 00:07:15,160
So cold...

77
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,240
I see.

78
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:19,830
Ice magic, yes...

79
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:22,210
What the hell is going on?

80
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:27,710
I think I may be at an advantage here.

81
00:07:27,970 --> 00:07:33,280
This weapon, Rossa Espada, 
softens anything and everything.

82
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:35,350
It is really, truly, unfortunate...

83
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:40,790
Natsu, pull yourself together!

84
00:07:42,100 --> 00:07:44,720
What's with these things? 
They won't come off!

85
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:48,020
I said pull it together, sheesh!

86
00:07:48,020 --> 00:07:48,900
Not a chance!

87
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:18,360
I-I'm saved...

88
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:21,550
Take a look at that!

89
00:08:25,140 --> 00:08:27,230
Oh, <i>thanks</i> for that.

90
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:29,650
Water?

91
00:08:30,970 --> 00:08:34,750
That's Edolas's magic! Like, whoa, right?

92
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:39,340
And this wonderful magic 
will be gone pretty soon...

93
00:08:39,340 --> 00:08:41,270
I don't even wanna think about it!

94
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:45,720
That's why you'll kill them?

95
00:08:49,750 --> 00:08:56,430
You'll kill my friends and the 
Exceeds for your convenience?

96
00:08:58,560 --> 00:08:59,800
That's right.

97
00:09:00,630 --> 00:09:04,100
They'll be sacrificed for the 
sake of our eternal magic supply.

98
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:05,600
Screw that.

99
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:10,060
My friends are still alive.

100
00:09:12,050 --> 00:09:14,230
And the Exceeds are still alive.

101
00:09:17,180 --> 00:09:21,390
Something's more important than 
whether or not there's magic power...

102
00:09:21,390 --> 00:09:23,370
It's called living.

103
00:09:27,750 --> 00:09:29,500
It's life!!!!

104
00:09:30,540 --> 00:09:31,880
Natsu...

105
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:41,470
Natsu, get down!

106
00:09:43,090 --> 00:09:45,480
Gate of the Water Bearer, I open thee!

107
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:47,180
Aquarius!

108
00:09:49,060 --> 00:09:50,290
Please!

109
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:51,650
I know already.

110
00:09:58,110 --> 00:09:59,190
The water...

111
00:09:59,190 --> 00:10:01,200
What's wrong, Aquarius?

112
00:10:01,820 --> 00:10:04,330
I cannot control this water!

113
00:10:06,340 --> 00:10:13,010
I told you once already... Everything 
in this amusement park is my weapon!

114
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:18,570
Lucy, take cover!

115
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:28,260
Your Highness, all the preparations 
have been completed.

116
00:10:28,260 --> 00:10:32,270
We have reached the final stage of Code ETD.

117
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:43,360
Farewell, God!

118
00:10:56,350 --> 00:11:00,580
The magic power we extracted 
from the Dragon Slayers

119
00:11:00,580 --> 00:11:05,870
can be thought of as giant chains enabling 
you to move the floating islands at will.

120
00:11:05,870 --> 00:11:09,590
Then, once the floating islands 
are under your control,

121
00:11:09,590 --> 00:11:15,810
all you need to do is simply ram that 
lacrima into those damn cats' kingdom...

122
00:11:17,540 --> 00:11:21,060
Do that, and the magic 
power will fuse together,

123
00:11:21,060 --> 00:11:25,600
and an eternity of magic power 
will rain down on our kingdom.

124
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:34,440
The Edolas magic spell, Dragon Chain Cannon.

125
00:11:34,990 --> 00:11:39,130
A device which utilizes the 
magic power of dragons.

126
00:11:39,130 --> 00:11:43,380
Presently, it cannot be used as a weapon.

127
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:45,640
Now, Your Highness...

128
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:48,260
The key to activate the 
Dragon Chain Cannon...

129
00:11:48,260 --> 00:11:50,180
Your Highness!

130
00:11:50,810 --> 00:11:52,940
Your Highness, wait!

131
00:11:53,330 --> 00:11:54,910
Hey, Coco!

132
00:11:54,910 --> 00:11:59,020
How many times have I told you 
not to run around near the king!

133
00:11:59,260 --> 00:12:00,610
Please stop this!

134
00:12:00,610 --> 00:12:03,400
Lily is there on that lacrima island!

135
00:12:11,490 --> 00:12:12,970
You ain't bad!

136
00:12:12,970 --> 00:12:15,350
So this is Earthland magic...

137
00:12:15,350 --> 00:12:17,220
It is quite intriguing.

138
00:12:18,380 --> 00:12:19,890
This is getting exciting!

139
00:12:19,890 --> 00:12:22,510
Finally, a guy that's actually near my level!

140
00:12:22,510 --> 00:12:25,060
This isn't the time to be enjoying yourself!

141
00:12:25,060 --> 00:12:26,820
And besides, you're heavy, Gajeel!

142
00:12:26,820 --> 00:12:28,450
Well, not as heavy as Lucy...

143
00:12:28,450 --> 00:12:30,610
You sure you should be sayin' that?

144
00:12:30,610 --> 00:12:32,380
Lucy's gonna pulverize you.

145
00:12:32,380 --> 00:12:33,980
I take back what I said!

146
00:12:33,980 --> 00:12:35,170
You can put me down.

147
00:12:35,170 --> 00:12:36,240
Aye!

148
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:39,850
You're Salamander's cat, yeah...

149
00:12:39,850 --> 00:12:45,410
I'll look forward to fightin' in 
the air when I find my own cat.

150
00:12:45,410 --> 00:12:46,490
Gajeel...

151
00:12:47,890 --> 00:12:50,420
Magic Charging Complete.

152
00:12:50,420 --> 00:12:53,620
Master Ma'am, reactivate!

153
00:12:54,250 --> 00:12:57,750
But damn, that's one big sword.

154
00:12:57,750 --> 00:12:58,330
Aye!

155
00:12:58,330 --> 00:13:03,780
If we measure it this way, 
it's 4 Panther Lily's big!

156
00:13:03,780 --> 00:13:06,180
Who gives a crap about it?

157
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:14,930
Chatting during a battle? 
You are overly confident.

158
00:13:17,900 --> 00:13:20,200
He chopped off some of the island!

159
00:13:20,690 --> 00:13:25,320
It ain't just big... The guy who's 
wielding it is skilled as well.

160
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:29,300
I'll make you nothing more than rust 
on my Great Sword, Master Ma'am!

161
00:13:29,300 --> 00:13:31,410
Earthland wizard!

162
00:13:31,710 --> 00:13:36,010
I see. But you know, rust is pretty.

163
00:13:36,010 --> 00:13:38,540
Aye! Gajeel's iron, after all!

164
00:13:42,070 --> 00:13:43,020
Here I go!

165
00:13:43,020 --> 00:13:44,210
Bring it!

166
00:13:50,380 --> 00:13:54,310
If you activate the plan now, 
Lily will be caught up in it!

167
00:13:58,040 --> 00:14:00,100
And what about it?

168
00:14:02,470 --> 00:14:04,020
He's our ally!

169
00:14:04,020 --> 00:14:09,130
Coco, he will be a martyr to 
our great Kingdom's future!

170
00:14:09,130 --> 00:14:10,350
But...

171
00:14:11,060 --> 00:14:14,080
I don't want Lily to die!

172
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:18,000
Who cares what happens to that damn Exceed?

173
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,900
No, no!

174
00:14:21,790 --> 00:14:22,920
I said no!

175
00:14:23,900 --> 00:14:25,330
What are you...

176
00:14:26,120 --> 00:14:28,300
Coco!

177
00:14:32,470 --> 00:14:35,930
You have always loved to run.

178
00:14:41,870 --> 00:14:47,190
And I loved to watch you run around...

179
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:56,910
Hand the key over to me.

180
00:15:03,250 --> 00:15:04,750
Coco!

181
00:15:05,170 --> 00:15:08,120
Bydo, after her! Right now!

182
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:09,300
Y-Yes, sire!

183
00:15:10,670 --> 00:15:13,260
It hurts! It hurts!

184
00:15:13,610 --> 00:15:16,910
I've never had my feet feel such pain!

185
00:15:17,130 --> 00:15:20,420
Even I want everlasting magic power!

186
00:15:20,740 --> 00:15:23,270
But I don't want Lily to die!

187
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:26,640
What'll I do? What'll I do?

188
00:15:45,380 --> 00:15:46,820
Where am I?

189
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:48,880
And hey, where's Lucy?

190
00:15:48,880 --> 00:15:49,760
You okay?

191
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:51,050
Hey!

192
00:15:51,580 --> 00:15:54,510
Natsu, here! I'm in here!

193
00:15:54,510 --> 00:15:56,260
Get me outta here!

194
00:15:56,260 --> 00:15:58,560
Why're you in a a place like that?

195
00:15:58,560 --> 00:16:00,000
How should I know?

196
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:03,250
Before I realized it, I was in this dark, 
cramped place and couldn't get out!

197
00:16:05,780 --> 00:16:07,670
What's with the face?

198
00:16:10,550 --> 00:16:13,000
What're you doing in that outfit?!

199
00:16:13,610 --> 00:16:14,530
Huh?!

200
00:16:14,790 --> 00:16:17,160
Costume actor box...

201
00:16:17,160 --> 00:16:22,610
Now, dress up in a wonderful outfit and set 
forth on your journey to Fairy Tale land!

202
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:24,290
Fairy Tale?

203
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:26,790
There's a dial here!

204
00:16:26,790 --> 00:16:28,680
Put me back to normal.

205
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:30,630
Righto!

206
00:16:46,230 --> 00:16:47,650
Stop playin' around!

207
00:16:47,650 --> 00:16:49,130
W-Wait...

208
00:16:55,150 --> 00:16:56,950
Now, <i>you</i> stop playin' around!

209
00:16:57,850 --> 00:17:01,200
Where'd you go, Earthland wizards?

210
00:17:01,990 --> 00:17:03,250
It's him!

211
00:17:03,910 --> 00:17:07,780
Being all hard-boiled in that 
getup doesn't work at all!

212
00:17:07,780 --> 00:17:09,750
Hurry up and change me back already!

213
00:17:11,570 --> 00:17:13,000
What?

214
00:17:13,960 --> 00:17:16,630
I just had a <i>great</i> idea...

215
00:17:19,850 --> 00:17:22,640
Whoa, were they blown far away...

216
00:17:23,180 --> 00:17:27,560
Those Earthland wizards talk big 
and act big, but they ain't...

217
00:17:27,560 --> 00:17:29,030
Hi!

218
00:17:29,270 --> 00:17:31,650
Onii-san!

219
00:17:43,790 --> 00:17:46,830
My sexy seduction plan was a giant flop!

220
00:17:46,830 --> 00:17:48,800
He didn't go for it!

221
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:51,290
And what the hell are these monsters?

222
00:17:55,170 --> 00:17:57,870
This is the Monster Academy.

223
00:17:57,870 --> 00:18:02,430
It's an attraction that gives you a 
peek at the school days of monsters!

224
00:18:03,620 --> 00:18:07,430
Whatever, just let me change 
back into my clothes!

225
00:18:07,670 --> 00:18:09,040
Lucy...

226
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:11,750
Natsu, hurry up and save me!

227
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:15,300
Crap! How can you be so incredibly unsexy?!

228
00:18:15,730 --> 00:18:16,940
That's what his problem is?

229
00:18:16,940 --> 00:18:20,080
And I thought it was such a great idea...

230
00:18:24,710 --> 00:18:26,830
I guess I just gotta go straight at him.

231
00:18:26,830 --> 00:18:30,080
You really plan on fighting me 
here in this Monster Academy?

232
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:33,340
This is my favorite place, 
I'll have you know.

233
00:18:33,340 --> 00:18:37,400
Oh, is it? Well, I like this place, too.

234
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:40,730
Mummy Bandage!

235
00:18:43,470 --> 00:18:48,090
Every monster in Monster 
Academy is my soldier!

236
00:18:48,090 --> 00:18:49,550
Like, whoa, right?

237
00:18:50,890 --> 00:18:52,730
This ain't nothin'!

238
00:18:55,630 --> 00:18:56,570
What?!

239
00:18:57,620 --> 00:18:59,490
Flames from his entire body?

240
00:18:59,530 --> 00:19:02,800
Wing Slash of the Fire Dragon!

241
00:19:05,410 --> 00:19:07,250
Franken Knuckle!

242
00:19:28,260 --> 00:19:29,600
What incredible power...

243
00:19:35,610 --> 00:19:37,690
Monster Troops, assemble!

244
00:19:38,390 --> 00:19:39,820
Bring him down!

245
00:19:41,970 --> 00:19:45,280
No!!

246
00:19:55,940 --> 00:19:58,310
Can you really win against these monsters?

247
00:20:09,220 --> 00:20:10,390
Ouch...

248
00:20:32,260 --> 00:20:36,330
What are you doing, monsters? Go!

249
00:21:03,230 --> 00:21:04,750
He's a real...

250
00:21:10,270 --> 00:21:11,870
...monster!

251
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:18,660
What's with these monsters?! Stay away!

252
00:21:26,940 --> 00:21:28,780
Huh? Where're the monsters?

253
00:21:28,780 --> 00:21:30,320
And who are you?

254
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:35,120
What happened to your feet?

255
00:21:35,120 --> 00:21:36,580
They're seriously injured!

256
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:40,140
I can't run any more...

257
00:21:40,140 --> 00:21:42,250
Coco, wait, would you?!

258
00:21:44,200 --> 00:21:45,600
Help me...

259
00:21:46,750 --> 00:21:48,010
This.

260
00:21:49,630 --> 00:21:53,510
That's right... This person 
is the girl from Earthland...

261
00:21:53,510 --> 00:21:56,490
It's no use, I can't give her the key...

262
00:21:56,490 --> 00:21:57,660
What'll I do?

263
00:22:01,070 --> 00:22:03,310
Hurry up and give me the key!

264
00:22:03,310 --> 00:22:04,340
Key?

265
00:22:04,340 --> 00:22:07,050
W-Why is he after my keys?

266
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:11,970
I won't give any of them to you!

267
00:22:11,970 --> 00:22:14,930
She's confused about something...

268
00:22:15,560 --> 00:22:16,930
Don't worry!

269
00:22:21,760 --> 00:22:24,540
'Cause I'll beat him for you!

270
00:23:56,030 --> 00:23:58,120
Oh? Where'd Lucy go?

271
00:23:58,120 --> 00:24:00,720
She ran off yelling somewhere.

272
00:24:00,720 --> 00:24:02,540
What's she playing around for?

273
00:24:02,540 --> 00:24:03,600
Whatever.

274
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:05,870
Gray and the guy with the 
chin ain't around, either.

275
00:24:05,870 --> 00:24:09,370
The chin person tripped on his chin 
and went flying and he gave chase.

276
00:24:09,370 --> 00:24:11,600
Huh? What? What's that mean?

277
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:13,470
The chin on the chin did what?

278
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:16,900
Next time: The Great River 
of Stars is for Pride...

279
00:24:16,900 --> 00:24:20,330
It's simple, the chin person 
went flying, like swoosh!

280
00:24:20,330 --> 00:24:21,710
A chin can fly?!

281
00:24:21,710 --> 00:24:25,160
You make it sound like 
only the chin is flying!

282
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:27,160


